RUSTENBURG – A 21-year-old man has been arrested for allegedly stoning another man to death in Atamelang, north of Delareyville, North West police said on Sunday. Lt-Col Amanda Funani said the man was arrested in connection with the murder of a 30-year-old man on Friday. “It is alleged that the suspect and the victim were from a local tavern and a fight ensured. The suspect assaulted the victim with stones. He was taken to a local clinic where he later died.” The arrested man was expected to appear in the Atamelang Magistrate’s Court on Monday. READ: Law on adultery stoning amended In an unrelated case, a 27–year-old woman was expected to appear in the Ga-Rankuwa Magistrate’s Court on Monday for the alleged murder of her 27-year-old husband. She allegedly stabbed her husband at their home after a fight broke out between them. “It is alleged the wife took out a knife and stabbed her husband. The victim was rushed to a local hospital where he later died,” Funani said. African News Agency